# Auto-overseer end-to-end smoke — STEP 4
# Status: PENDING — cannot run in the session that created the hook.

WHY PENDING
Claude Code snapshots hook configuration at session start. overseer-on-stop.sh
was added to .claude/settings.json during this session, so it is NOT live in
this session. End-to-end behaviour cannot be observed here. Confirmed in the
STEP 1 spike — see stop-hook-mechanics-2026-05-21.log.

HOW TO RUN (owner, after reviewing + committing the staged changes)
1. Restart Claude Code (new session) so the Stop-hook snapshot reloads and
   overseer-on-stop.sh becomes live.
2. Ensure an active slice exists: a non-_template *.md in .overseer/slice/.
3. End a turn with a unit-completion line — e.g. paste pytest output
   containing "N passed", or a sentence saying "tests pass".
4. Observe: the next turn should begin with the injected OVERSEER CHECKPOINT
   audit prompt (re-read the slice contract, apply the 12-check, emit verdict).
5. Let the audit run; confirm it emits "OVERSEER_PASS / OVERSEER_BLOCK /
   OVERSEER_ESCALATE" on its own line, and — on PASS — appends a
   .overseer/ledger.md entry.
6. Confirm the turn AFTER the verdict ends normally (recursion guard: the
   hook must NOT re-fire on the verdict turn).

PASS CRITERIA
- Checkpoint injected after a unit-completion turn.
- No re-fire after the verdict turn (recursion guard holds).
- No injection on a turn with no completion pattern.

